{
  "doc_id": "839",
  "text": "Not all studies, however, have demonstrated postprandial impairment of FMD following a high-fat meal [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The reason for this discrepancy is unclear, and could be related to differences in the patient population studied or in the specific type of fat consumed. For example, [CITATION_5] demonstrated a meal high in oxidised fat, but not uncooked fat, impaired FMD; however, in a subsequent study no effect of heat modified fat was observed [CITATION_6] .",
